FBIS4-36155 "drnes109_j_94008" FBIS-NES-94-109 Daily Report 7 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Sanaa `Source' Warns YSP Against Violation Sanaa `Source' Warns YSP Against Violation JN0706110394 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 1030 GMT 7 Jun 94 JN0706110394 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Statement by "a military source"; place and date not given] [Text] While our brave Armed Forces -- the forces of unity and legitimacy -- have fully complied with the declaration of cease-fire on all axes as of 2400 yesterday [6 June], in implementation of Security Council Resolution 924, the rebellious separatist gang, led by the [Yemeni] Socialist Party [YSP], violated the cease-fire resolution and continued its aggression against our Armed Forces. The aircraft affiliated with this criminal gang this morning carried out aggressive raids against our Armed Forces positions on all axes. The source warned against this violation of the cease-fire by the rebellious separatist gang, which constitutes blatant defiance of the international will and reflects the adventurous aggressive behavior of this separatist rebellious gang.
